5000|$|A durable {{solution}} for an unaccompanied or <b>separated</b> <b>child</b> {{is understood as}} “a sustainable solution that ensures that the unaccompanied or <b>separated</b> <b>child</b> {{is able to develop}} into adulthood, in an environment which will meet his or her needs and fulfil his or her rights as defined by the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child and will not put the child at risk of persecution or serious harm. Because the durable solution will have fundamental long-term consequences for the unaccompanied or <b>separated</b> <b>child,</b> it will be subject to a best interests’ determination. A durable solution also ultimately allows the child to acquire, or to re-acquire, the full protection of a state.” ...|$|E
